The paper discusses methods for enriching information from knowledge graphs, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The evaluation of these methods involves the use of various scores, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a new evaluation method that aims to address the shortcomings of existing scores, which is a topic that falls under natural language processing (cs.CL).
